<br>
As a cleric there is nothing more darn right aweful than a ranger or a monk  who is not the MA and  has to be tossed celestial healing over and over again along with a tank needing CH or a chanter getting resisted ..I aint complaining ..it is my job but some things can stand for improvement.<br>
I play with mostly those who still could learn a thing or too or obtain an item or two. If I wasnt learning something I might fall asleep.<br>
<br>
Monks need to know when to play dead...rangers need to know how to jolt and rogues best know how to evade.<br>
Dont make your cleric a nerviouos wreck cause you can mend and heal when the fight is over. SK's just lifetap away...only God knows where their life bar will end up. <br>
<br>
As a ranger, who knows there gear, I will not play MA unless pressured. I dont train for that regardless if I can do it or not. If I am pulling when I play in a group aggro becomes an even bigger problem.<br>
<br>
Rarely do I jolt solo anymore but I do use it cause it stuns.<br>
My ranger has been in a few groups where he has had trouble with getting aggro.;...First he used jolting blades with cinder jolt as back up....If that dont work then he has to quit catching the aggroe with his dots and nukes<br>
this is hard if he has KEI and sees the mobs dropping much faster with them..BUT AGGRO SUCKS...backing off to nuke and jolt can work even if your summoned constantly, <br>
Immolate always puts you to the top of the mobs hate list ..as do the direct damage spells....you see it in his face... he summons you..etc etc...The only way to get off his hate list is to jolt...be it jolt,  jolting blades, or  cinder jolt....heck use them all if the warrior is not keeping the aggro. <br>
Snare and drones of doom dont change aggro on the mobs ( that I have seen) enough to worry about them or to stop using them.<br>
Yeah rangers are great damage dealers but with a ranger as a main, I hate to have my alt cleric wishing any ranger was a rogue..<br>
