font color=#FF0000>(9/30/02 7:14:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1427.topic&index=20>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rangers uses</span><hr size=1> My opinion....such it is.<br>
A ranger, up to level 50, is pretty much melee DPS.  <br>
<br>
After 50, Archery becomes a legitimate source of damage as non-moving targets start to take double damage.  <br>
<br>
Level 55 brings Trueshot which is great for 2 minutes, but it's not something that you want to rely on.  It's only after many AA points (Endless Quiver and Archery Mastery 1 ... at least) that archery starts to become even close to melee output (assuming that the character has epics or equivalent).  At Archery Mastery 2 and Endless Quiver, the ranger can avoid aggro easily and do damage equal to or higher than the average dps.  Archery mastery 3 allows the character to do more damage continually with the bow, assuming that the player does not have VERY high end weapons and / or the mob is correctly positioned.<br>
<br>
So...when is a ranger an archer as opposed to a melee character?  I switched at level 60 and 27 AA points.<br>
<br>
At a minimum, below level 50, let em swing their blades and manage aggro.  Any player who has done their time in the ranger trenches knows aggro and should be able to handle it.<br>
<br>
Ramblings of a Ranger....<br>
